<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">You list some good equipment (below), but this person is only level 27, on the server I play on Mammoth Cloak is at least 2k plat, Gatorscale leggings are about 800, so those are probably a trifle out of reach at 27 (unless the player wants to spend a great deal of time buying low and selling high, for example in East Commons).<p>

Also 2 chipped bone bracers would be 1000 plat (about), as opposed to about 300 (or less) for the pair of polished bone bracelets (for that matter, at 27, he/she can get the polished bone bracelets themself if they don't mind killing evil eyes over and over, where chipped bone is out of reach at this point.  Also, I got the Ivy Braided Cords at that level, because someone gave them to me, but cash is still something of an issue there, so the lizzy mantle might be a good option to tide them over at a much lower cost (about 300 - 400 plat vs. 50 on my server).  This person must not be a twink with the equip they have, so at 27, they really need to be saving a lot of their cash for those level 29 spells (at which point they can earn as much cash as they want to spend time teleporting.<p>

I just thought knap's advice was a little more in tune with what an average, non-twinked, level 27 druid could afford. (Actually, for me, that was still more then I could afford at that point)<p>

You (Jessy) said: I would get an ivy etched cords, (+5 wis, 4 ac) NOT a lizzy mantle, which only has 3 wis. I would also get Chipped Bone Bracers insted of Polished, because CBBs have more wisdom and armor class. Also, the wisdom earrings you are referring to are THREE wisdom earrings, not four. There's no such thing as 4 wi earrings. Also, if you have the cash, I'd get a Mammoth Cloak, and Gatorscale Legs. You definately cannot afford 15k - 20k for Golden Efreeti Boots.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
