<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Im a lvl 30 druid on torvonnilous, a relatively new server. If you want money for items, get a partner for EE's and camp them for PBB's and money until 24. Then you should be rich enough to buy spells and several +wis items. Then camp the hermit in SK. He carries plenty of FS weapons. Then kite some avos til 29. Then kill thistle for the braided ivy cords. After that i went to perma, anbd camped the goblin alchemist for the mammoth hide cloak. The camp is hell, but well worth it. While yer in perma you might as well camp the preacher room too, for a runed circlet. Any of these you can do by yerself or with a partner at 29. Ive done all this and by 30 i had a wisdom of 170, with almost no help from a guild or higher lvls. <p>

Cidris<br>
Druid<br>
