<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">This is for info on the Testament of Vanear quest.  Yes, it is an AWESOME druid item, being +10 wis +10 mana, secondary hand.  Unfortunately, the quest can be VERY long.  First, journey on over to Qeynos and talk to someone named Moodoro in the bar.  If your faction isn't good enough, just give him 2gp.  He will then give you the testament, but it is missing 2 pages.  Next, continually give him 4gp until you receive the "Jester Card".  I have heard that it is now possible just to give him back other cards without having to spend a lot of money, but I haven't tried it.  Anyway, once you have the Jester Card, give it back to him.  He will then complain and reward you with the first page of the Testament.  Now for the hard part.  You need to head over to highpass and go to the smuggler camp.  To reach it, you must swim through a semi-hidden cave.  You will know immediately that it is the right one.  Then, follow the path up until you reach the forge.  A named smuggler "Dyllin Starsine" spawns here once every 6 hours and 45 minutes.  This is the man you need to kill, as the second page is on his body.  There are lots of things that make this hard, however.  First, go /con the "s smuggler".  See that?  She's around level 40-45 and WILL kill you if she sees you attacking Dyllin.  She follows a set path around the camp that gives you exactly 2 minutes to kill Dyllin before she returns and gives you a 300 hp present.  As if that weren't bad enough, Dyllin is ALWAYS camped, so you will probably have to spend a solid day of camping just to get a turn. Then, after sitting at that spot for 7 hours, half the time high level characters log in 10 minutes before he spawns and KS you.<br>
     Well, now that we have that out of the way, I'll tell you how to kill him.  This is coming from a Druid's POV, but it shouldn't be much different with any other class.  First off, I waited until 19 to even try, because you need careless lightning in order to do enough damage in a short enough time period.  Next, you will need enough mana to get in 2-4 harmonies, 1-3 grasping roots, and around 4 careless lightnings.  At this point, I had around 127 wisdom, which shouldn't be hard for most people, because this is my first character and I'm not twinked at all.  Anyway, next I'm going to tell my experiences trying to kill the fiend.  First time I arrive-he's camped, so I go kill stuff till he spawns.  The guy kills him and I set up shop.  At this point, I had reached level 20 and had tracking to improve.  So...for the next 6 hours, I talked to people, my guild, and practiced foraging, tracking, sense heading, and fishing in the pond.  Once I had exhausted all of those, I moved on to maxxing out my casting skills.  By that time, Dyllin popped.  This is what I did-Frantically harmonied all of the bystanding smugglers, waited for the s to leave, then rooted Dyllin and began DD'ing him.  With one left, the s returned and began wailing on me.  I ran away completely oom and with 23 hp left.  Somehow, Dyllin and the s ran into each other and got stuck, so I medded to just enough to get in one last Lightning, which killed Dyllin.  I rushed over and began looting the corpse.  Too bad for me the s was now unstuck and she finished me off.  Even worse, I went LD trying to reload, and by the time I got back someone had already looted the corpse.  Back to those casting skills.<br>
    6 hours later-A 19 cleric joins me to help camp, and shortly after a 20 warrior does too.  10 minutes before Dyllin spawns, a lvl 39 Druid named DENEORN (on Luclin server, any and all are welcome to bug him to death with repeated "KS KS KS KS KS KS KS" tells) appears, yells at us, laughs, and takes Dyllin from us.  I stand around and complain for a while, petition, and back to the casting skills.<br>
    ANOTHER 6 hours later- I'm sitting here with the cleric waiting on the spawn when a level 55 wizzy hears my tales of woe and decides to help out.  FINALLY, Dyllin pops, she kills him, and I get my page!!!!!!  Anyway, the moral of this story is: DO NOT ATTEMPT TO KILL DYLLIN BY YOURSELF UNLESS YOU ARE ABSOLUTELY SURE YOU CAN GET THE JOB DONE.  DO NOT LISTEN TO ANY OTHER POSTINGS TELLING YOU THAT A LEVEL 14 CAN KILL HIM EASILY, BECAUSE THAT IS COMPLETE BS!  TRUST ME AND GOOD HUNTING.<br>
    Sorry to take up so much room, but in the 2 months I have been playing EQ, I have learned that people WILL screw you over in a second and people WILL take advantage of ANY kindness you EVER give.  I just had to post my feelings and hopefully prevent any of you other honest, non-ksing people from being screwed on this quest.  Thanks and sorry if I got on anyone's nerves.<p>

PS-To Bombair, the most trustworthy person I know, thanks for giving back my enforcer over and over after all of those LD's and luck on the 1hb  ;)<hr>Dillan Dawnseeker<br>
24th Druid<br>
Luclin<br>
Go Phoenix Raiders!!!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
