<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Starting at level 19 (after i had bought all the spells for the next level), i made a list from eqdruids.com  (equipment:wisdom items) of all the wisdom items that were below 100plat.<br>
     Jasper Gold Earrings - +3wis earrings - i got for 40 plat a pair<br>
     Black Iron Medallion - +3wis, +3int 20 plat<br>
     Polished Bone Bracelet - i got one for 100 plat, the other for 90 plat<br>
     Split Paw Hide Gloves - +2wis, +3 dex - 10 plat from a very kind mage<br>
     prayer cloth of tunare - +3wis, +3int - 35 plat<br>
     Savant Cap - +3wis, +3int - 35 plat<br>
     I can't remember the rings, maybe +2 or +3 wis<br>
Once i had 100 plat saved, I watched the auctions continually, & always offer a little bit below what the seller asks.  I try to be really nice & make a lot of jokes so the seller at least like me.  & if they don't wanna sell, i wish them well & wait a couple days.<br>
I also made a auc hot key for when i traveled, that listed all the stuff i wanted.    <p>

Because i have a family and my playing time is very limited (3 hrs/5times a week), i can't camp for my equipment.  i have to make do with what i can buy.  <p>

Once i had maxed out all the stuff under 100 plat, i repeated the process with items a little bit more expensive.<br>
     Foreman's Tunic +3wis, +3str  150 plat<br>
     Platinum Arm band +3wis, +3str 125 plat<br>
     Silver ruby Veil +3wis, +3 str 200 plat<p>

Now i am level 30 (what HELL!) with wisdom of 165, which is not the greatest, but is good i think.<p>

Also, if you can't camp for the testament, like me, the Bone Talisman quest is do-able, for +4 wis. save vs. magic +10.  You need the aviak charm & a tiger skin & a fang from a snake in east commons.  research this quest for better details than i have. <p>

My point is that if you know what you want, & you are diligent & patient, & try to make good bargains, you can get decent wisdom without a lot of camping.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
